track.name: Do the Rump
comments: Reminds me of the Black Keys................................Doh
this album is still their best... each one following has been phenomenal but the Big Come Up rips!!!
Now 'dem some DAMN fine licks.  I was rockin' and ROLLIN' at work listening to this.  Love me some blues, love me THESE blues.

Love this band. Love this song. I remember when I first heard this album, it took me a while to realize that the singer wasn't some 80 year old black dude, but rather just some 20 something year old white dude. Ha!!
Reminds me of The Beatles' Why Don't We Do it in the Road <3
I be rumpin'.....with a little bumpin'....Yeah..
I wonder why the original isn't among the related tracks? --> Richard Johnston (on: Foot Hill Stomp)
